<p>I am using Jackson library. I have number of java objects which are nothing but the wrapper for jsonNode. So want to convert these list of jsonNodes into single jsonNode. how can i do that. i tried this  </p>  <pre><code>   public JsonNode converter(List&lt;? extends Base&gt; objList){     List&lt;String&gt; jsonList=new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;();     try      {     for (Base raObject : objList) {         ObjectWriter ow = new ObjectMapper().writer().withDefaultPrettyPrinter();         String json = ow.writeValueAsString(raObject);         jsonList.add(json);     }      return JsonHelper.convert(jsonList);      }catch(Exception e)     {          System.out.println("Error occured while converting objectlist to jsonNode::"+e);          return null;     }        } </code></pre>  <p>this is not working. ithere any other way?</p>